  <section>
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para>The Atom Syndication Format is <quote>an XML-based Web content and
    metadata syndication format</quote><xref linkend="rfc4287" />. It is most
    useful for advanced clients including:</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Desktop management clients</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Network management systems</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para>Intercloud communication</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>The following is an example of an OCCI resource in
    <computeroutput>application/occi+xml</computeroutput> format:</para>

    <screen>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt;
&lt;entry xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:occi="http://purl.org/net/occi"&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;http://example.com/products/1234&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;Resource #1&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;summary&gt;Web resource for demonstration purposes&lt;/summary&gt;
  &lt;author&gt;
     &lt;name&gt;Acme, Inc.&lt;/name&gt;
  &lt;/author&gt;
  &lt;updated&gt;2005-07-31T12:29:29Z&lt;/updated&gt;
  &lt;occi:etag&gt;46dd20-23-464015228e7c0&lt;/occi:etag&gt;
  &lt;category term="widget" scheme="http://example.com/products" label="Widgets" /&gt;
  &lt;link rel="alternate" href="http://example.com/products/1234" title="Link to myself" /&gt;
&lt;/entry&gt;</screen>
